com.ichess.game

Class FEN

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ichess.game.FEN

  • public class FEN
extends java.lang.Object
    Used to import and export games from the FEN notation. The FEN specification is used to record a status of a game, so it can be continued at a later time.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Ran Berenfeld
    See Also:
    FEN notation specification.

      • getFENPosition

        public static java.lang.String getFENPosition(Game game)
        Returns the FEN position of the given Game. The FEN position is the first token of the FEN string, containing only the pieces position.
        Parameters:
        game - the game whose position is returned
        Returns:
        The FEN position of the given Game. null on error.

      • loadGame

        public static Game loadGame(java.lang.String fen,
            boolean startGame,
            int gkind)
        Loads the given FEN string into the given game. All the game moves are taken back. If startGame is false, then the FEN may be an invalid game position.
        Parameters:
        fen - - The FEN string to load.
        startGame - - If true, FEN position is validated as a valid chess position.
        Returns:
        true on success. otherwise false.
